The paper deals with non-convex learning problems and provides a nonasymptotic analysis of Stochastic Gradient Langevin Dynamics (SGLD) algorithm. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses diffusion processes and transportation cost inequalities, which are common in the fields of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Information Theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the convergence of SGLD to a stationary distribution, which is relevant to the field of Nonlinear Dynamics (cs.NE) and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
